#  for modern authorization: define roles/permissions/resources,
#  generate policy code for OPA Rego / OpenFGA / Cedar / Permit
#  Cloud, run policy tests, sync with GitOps, query the PDP
#  (Policy Decision Point) sidecar.  Used by developers
#  integrating fine-grained authorization into their apps via
#  Permit's hosted backend or self-hosted OPA/OpenFGA/Cedar.
#  Sister tools: opa (in corpus via _opa + STOCK Kubernetes
#  distros; Open Policy Agent — the canonical policy engine),
#  conftest (in corpus via _conftest; OPA-based config tester),
#  cedar (AWS Cedar policy language — emerging IAM standard),
#  openfga (in corpus via _openfga; Zanzibar-inspired relation-
#  based authz), fga-cli (OpenFGA CLI), oso (Oso authorization
#  framework — in corpus via _oso), keto (ORY Keto), kong-
#  authorization (Kong gateway).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 19th TypeScript/Node CLI library
#  — Vadim Demedes's **pastel** (vadimdemedes/pastel).
#  TypeScript-Node ecosystem now has 19 documented CLI libraries
