#
#  pastel distinctive features:
#    - FILE-SYSTEM-BASED ROUTING (Next.js style) — each `.tsx`
#      file in `source/commands/` becomes a CLI subcommand
#      automatically; subdirectories nest as sub-trees.  Naming
#      conventions: `index.tsx` → root, `[arg].tsx` → positional
#      catch-all, `_app.tsx` → wrapper component (like Next.js
#      `_app.tsx`)
#    - ZOD-TYPED OPTIONS — `options = z.object({...})` schema
#      describing every flag with Zod's type system; `z.string
#      ()`/`z.number()`/`z.boolean()`/`z.enum([...])`/`z.array
#      (...)` etc.  Pastel reads the schema at build time and
#      generates the CLI parser
#    - INK-RENDERED UI — default-export React component is
#      rendered to terminal via Ink (38,683-stars React-for-
#      terminal renderer); enables FULL REACT FEATURES IN CLI
#      (hooks, state, effects, conditional rendering, components
#      from `@inkjs/ui`, animations via `ink-spinner`, etc.)
#    - COMMANDER UNDER THE HOOD — pastel uses TJ Holowaychuk's
#      commander.js for actual argv parsing; Zod schema is
#      compiled to commander's `.option()` / `.argument()` calls
#      at build time
#    - `argument()` / `option()` HELPERS — `import { argument,
#      option } from 'pastel'` provides typed helpers for
#      `.describe(...)` to attach CLI-specific metadata to Zod
#      fields (description, alias, default, etc.)
#    - `_app.tsx` ROOT WRAPPER — like Next.js `pages/_app.tsx`,
#      `commands/_app.tsx` exports a wrapper component that
#      renders around every subcommand (useful for layout/
#      auth/loading boundaries)
#    - AUTO --help / --version — generated from `package.json`
#      version + Zod schema descriptions
#    - SCAFFOLD VIA `create-pastel-app` — `npm create
#      pastel-app my-cli` scaffolds a project with TypeScript +
#      linter + tests pre-configured
#    - TYPESCRIPT-FIRST — Zod-inferred types for the `options`
#      prop give full type-safety in React components without
#      manual type annotations
#    - INSPIRED BY Next.js (file-system routing + `_app.tsx`
#      wrapper pattern) + React Server Components (default
#      export = page/command component) + Vadim's prior Ink
#      design (React-for-terminal philosophy)
#  Distinct from R236 commander (TJ chained-builder — pastel
#  USES commander internally), R237 oclif (Heroku/Salesforce
