#  gluegun (Infinite Red TOOLBOX), R422 cleye (privatenumber's
#  type-constructor-as-type-spec), R428 @caporal/core (Mathieu
#  Robin's enterprise framework), R432 @effect/cli (Effect-TS
#  algebraic effect system), R433 @stricli/core (Bloomberg LP's
#  zero-deps).  TypeScript-Node documented libraries so far:
#  commander, oclif, yargs, meow, minimist, cac, clipanion, arg,
#  mri, sade, citty, cmd-ts, gluegun, cleye, @caporal/core,
#  @effect/cli, @stricli/core, pastel (this round)... 19 total.
#  pastel's distinguishing feature vs all other TS-Node libs:
#  pastel is the ONLY ONE that combines FILE-SYSTEM-BASED
#  ROUTING (Next.js style) WITH REACT-RENDERED TERMINAL UI (Ink)
#  in a SINGLE FRAMEWORK.  pastel's approach: NEXT.JS-FOR-CLI
